{"title_page": "Deon Thomas", "text_new": "{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name = Deon Thomas\n| image =\n| position = [[forward (basketball)|Forward]]\n| league = \n| team = \n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 9\n| weight_lbs = 238\n| nationality = American / Israeli\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1971|2|24}} \n| birth_place = [[Chicago, Illinois]]\n| high_school = [[Simeon Career Academy|Simeon]] (Chicago, Illinois)\n| college = [[Illinois Fighting Illini men's basketball|Illinois]] (1990\u20131994)\n| draft_year  = 1994\n| draft_round = 2\n| draft_pick  = 28\n| draft_team   = [[Dallas Mavericks]]\n| career_start = 1994\n| career_end = 2008\n| years1   = 1994\u20131995\n| team1    = [[B\u00e0squet Manresa]]  \n| years2   = 1995\u20131996\n| team2    = [[CB Sant Josep|Girona]] \n| years3   = 1996\u20131997\n| team3    = [[Baloncesto M\u00e1laga|Unicaja M\u00e1laga]] \n| years4   = 1997\u20131998\n| team4    = [[CB Sevilla|Caja San Fernando]] \n| years5   = 1998\u20131999\n| team5    = [[Maccabi Rishon LeZion (basketball)|Maccabi Rishon LeZion]] \n| years6   = 1999\u20132001\n| team6    = [[CB Gran Canaria|Gran Canaria]] \n| years7   = 2001\u20132003\n| team7    = [[C\u00e1ceres CB|C\u00e1ceres]] \n| years8   = 2003\n| team8    = [[T\u00fcrk Telekom B.K.|T\u00fcrk Telekom]] \n| years9   = 2003\u20132005\n| team9    = [[Maccabi Tel Aviv B.C.|Maccabi Tel Aviv]] \n| years10   = 2005\u20132006\n| team10    = [[Gymnastikos S. Larissas BC|Gymnastikos S. Larissas]]  \n| years11   = 2006\n| team11    = [[PBC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]] \n| years12   = 2006\u20132007\n| team12    = [[Maccabi Giv'at Shmuel]]  \n| years13   = 2007\u20132008\n| team13    = [[Maccabi Haifa B.C.|Maccabi Haifa]]  \n| highlights = \n* 2\u00d7 [[Euroleague Basketball|Euroleague]] champion ([[2003\u201304 Euroleague|2004]], [[2004\u201305 Euroleague|2005]])\n* [[McDonald's All-American]] ([[1989 McDonald's All-American Boys Game|1989]])\n* First-team [[Parade All-America Boys Basketball Team|''Parade'' All-American]] (1989)\n* [[Illinois Mr. Basketball]] (1989)\n}}\n'''Deon La velle Thomas''' (born February 24, 1971) is an American-Israeli former [[basketball]] player.<ref>[http://www.eurobasket.com/player.asp?Cntry=ISR&PlayerID=5145&AmNotSure=1]</ref> As a high school player, he led his team to the [[Chicago Public High School League|Chicago Public League]] title, and was named [[Illinois Mr. Basketball]].  As a college player at the [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign|University of Illinois]], he finished his career as the all-time leading scorer in [[Illinois Fighting Illini|Fighting Illini]] history. Selected by the [[Dallas Mavericks]] with the 28th selection of the [[1994 NBA Draft]], he \"opted\" to play professional basketball in Europe and Israel.\n\n==High school career==\nThomas was a star basketball player at [[Chicago]]'s [[Simeon Career Academy|Neal F. Simeon Vocational High School]], graduating in 1989. As a junior in 1988, he led the Wolverines to the [[Chicago Public High School League|Chicago Public League]] title. As a senior, he was named [[Illinois Mr. Basketball]] and played in the [[McDonald's All-American Game]], which also featured future [[National Basketball Association|NBA]] star [[Shaquille O'Neal]].<ref>[https://www.basketball-reference.com/awards/mcdonalds.html]</ref>\n\n==College career==\nThomas played [[college basketball]] at the [[University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign|University of Illinois]].  Thomas finished his career as the all-time leading scorer in [[Illinois Fighting Illini|Fighting Illini]] history, with 2129 career points scored and an 18.0 points per game scoring average.  Thomas is the only men's basketball player in Illinois history to score at least 2000 career points.  Thomas was elected to the \"[[Illinois Fighting Illini men's basketball#All-Century Team|Illini Men's Basketball All-Century Team]]\" in 2004.\n\n==Professional career==\nThomas was selected by the [[Dallas Mavericks]] with the 28th selection of the [[1994 NBA Draft]].  Thomas attended mini camp but never played in the [[National Basketball Association|NBA]], having opted to play professional basketball in Europe and Israel. Thomas played two years in [[Israel]] for [[Maccabi Tel Aviv]], winning the Israeli championship, the Israeli cup, and the Euroleague championship twice. Thomas didn't play in the 2005 Final Four due to a  broken leg. This injury forced him to leave Maccabi Tel Aviv. He then joined the [[Greece|Greek]] team [[Gymnastikos S. Larissas BC|Gymnastikos S. Larissas]], the [[Bulgaria]]n team [[CSKA Sofia]], and then returned to Israel where he played for [[Givat Shmuel]]. He then played for [[Maccabi Haifa]], also in Israel.<ref>[http://www.mhbasket.co.il/playerEng.asp?id=32&lang=en Maccabi Haifa<!-- Bot generated title -->]{{Dead link|date=July 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nHe is one of the most successful American pros of all time in the European leagues.  Thomas has passed on several opportunities to play in the NBA.  On 13 November 2006, in an interview for Bulgarian newspaper ''Tema Sport'' and Bulgarian television \"Channel 3\", Deon Thomas denied any wrongdoing and swore that he didn't receive anything from University of Illinois, as [[Bruce Pearl]] had claimed. He said the decision to play for Illinois was made by his grandmother.\n\n==Coaching/Announcing Career==\nIn 2009, Thomas became the men's basketball head coach at [[Lewis and Clark Community College]] in [[Godfrey, Illinois]]. In April 2014, Thomas was named as an assistant basketball coach at the University of Illinois-Chicago. In 2016, he was hired by [[Fighting Illini Sports Network]] to call men's basketball games with Doug Altenberger.\n\n==Personal life==\nThomas is now an Israeli citizen, and is married to an Israeli.<ref>[http://articles.chicagotribune.com/keyword/deon-thomas]</ref><ref>[http://www.haaretz.com/print-edition/sports/basketball-maccabi-can-count-on-deon-thomas-1.61248]</ref>\n\n==Honors==\n===High School===\n* 1988 - IHSA 1st Team All-State\n\n* 1988 - [[Illinois High School Association|IHSA]] State Tournament All-Tournament Team<ref>{{cite web |title=1988 Class AA Boys Summary |url=https://www.ihsa.org/archive/bkb/mm/1988baa.htm |website=ihsa.org |accessdate=May 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\n* 1989 - IHSA 1st Team All-State\n\n* 1989 - [[Parade Magazine]] [[Parade_All-America_Boys_Basketball_Team#1980\u20131989|1st Team All-American]]<ref>[https://basketball.realgm.com/player/Deon-Thomas/Summary/1559 Basketball.RealGM.com]</ref>\n\n* 1989 - [[1989 McDonald's All-American Boys Game|McDonald's All-American]]<ref>[https://basketballmuseumofillinois.com/history/15-history/49-boys-mcdonald-s-all-americans BasketballMuseumOfIllinois.com]</ref><ref>[https://www.basketball-reference.com/awards/mcdonalds.html Basketball-Reference.com]</ref>\n\n* 1989 - [[Illinois Mr. Basketball]]\n\n* 2015 - Inducted into the Illinois Basketball Coaches Association's Hall of Fame as a player.<ref>[http://basketballmuseumofillinois.com/hall-of-fame/players/19-hof-players/187-deon-thomas IBCA Hall of Fame]</ref>\n\n===College===\n* 1991 - 3rd Team All-[[Big Ten Conference|Big Ten]]\n\n* 1992 - Illini Team Co-Captain<ref>{{cite web |title=2018\u201319 Illinois basketball record book |url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/sidearm.sites/fightingillini.com/documents/2018/10/5/2018_19_ILLINI_MBB_Record_Book.pdf#page=84 |website=fightingillini.com |accessdate=May 2, 2019 |page=84}}</ref>\n\n* 1992 - Illini MVP\n\n* 1992 - 2nd Team All-Big Ten\n\n* 1993 - Illini Team Co-Captain\n\n* 1993 - Illini MVP\n\n* 1993 - 2nd Team All-Big Ten\n\n* 1994 - Illini Team Co-Captain\n\n* 1994 - Illini MVP\n\n* 1994 - 2nd Team All-Big Ten\n\n* 1994 - Honorable Mention [[1994 NCAA Men's Basketball All-Americans|All American]]\n\n* 2004 - Elected to the \"[[Illinois Fighting Illini men's basketball#All-Century Team|Illini Men's Basketball All-Century Team]]\".\n\n* 2008 - Honored as one of the thirty-three [[Illinois_Fighting_Illini_men%27s_basketball#Honored_jerseys|honored jerseys]] which hang in the [[State Farm Center]] to show regard for being the most decorated basketball players in the University of Illinois' history.\n\n* 2019 - Inducted into the Illinois Athletics Hall of Fame<ref>[http://uillinois_microsites.sidearmsports.com/halloffame/deonthomas.html Illinois Athletics Hall of Fame]</ref>\n\n==College statistics==\n===University of Illinois===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=text-align:center\" \"font-size:95%;\"\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Season\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Games\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Points\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |PPG\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Field Goals\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Attempts\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Avg\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Free Throws\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Attempts\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Avg\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Rebounds\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Avg\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Assists\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |APG\n! width=40px style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Illinois Fighting Illini}}; text-align:center\" |Blocks\n! width=